<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="180" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[241,1074,277,432]" pageId="27" pageNumber="180">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[267,376,277,298]" pageId="27" pageNumber="180">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Sasaji (1982 b)" authorityName="Sasaji" authorityYear="1982" box="[656,961,277,299]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Scymnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chujoi" subGenus="Pullus">
<emphasis box="[656,676,278,299]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="180">S.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[692,715,278,299]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="180">P.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[732,797,278,299]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="180">chujoi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sasaji &amp; Additions" box="[805,961,277,298]" pageId="27" pageNumber="180" refId="ref25484" refString="Sasaji, H. 1982 b. Additions to the Japanese fauna of the coccinellid tribe Scymnini (Coleoptera). [pp 63 - 72]. Special Issue to the Memory of Retirement of Emeritus Professor Michio Chujoˆ. Nagoya, Japan." type="book" year="1982">Sasaji (1982b)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but in the latter, the maxillary palpus terminal segment is nearly parallel­sided, the median piece of tegmen is thick in lateral aspect, and the postcoxal line of the first abdominal sternite is evenly arcuate. It is also similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Moll.)" baseAuthorityName="Moll." class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Scymnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrugatus" subGenus="Pullus">
<emphasis box="[890,910,358,379]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="180">S.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[926,949,358,379]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="180">P.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[964,1073,358,379]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="180">ferrugatus</emphasis>
(Moll.)
</taxonomicName>
illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bielawski" box="[476,662,384,405]" pageId="27" pageNumber="180" pagination="381 - 460" refId="ref22954" refString="Bielawski, R. 1984. Coccinellidae (Coleoptera) of Mongolia. Annales of Zoologici, Warszawa 38 (14): 381 - 460." type="journal article" year="1984">Bielawski (1984)</bibRefCitation>
, but in the latter the apical 1/5 of the elytron is orange­brown and the apex of sipho has a long thread­like appendix.
</paragraph>
